Information for Prospective Students - January 2026 Intake
QualiTEST Incorporated invites applications for our upcoming Allied Health Training Programs beginning in January 2026. Our programs are designed to prepare students for meaningful careers in healthcare through high-quality academic instruction, hands-on practical training, and national certification.

Entry Requirements

1
Entry Requirements
To be eligible for registration, applicants must possess a minimum of three (3) or four (4) Caribbean Examinations Council (CXC) subjects, as outlined below:

Note : Individuals currently working in healthcare may be considered for admission based on relevant experience, even if they do not meet the full academic requirements.

Important Dates

1
Important Dates
Orientation: Mid-November 2025

Program Commencement: January 2026

Orientation is mandatory before registration and gives prospective students an opportunity to:

Learn about each program and its career pathways

Meet instructors and staff

Understand the registration process, tuition, and blended learning format

Learning Format

2
Learning Format
Our programs are delivered through a blended learning model, combining:

Online classes via our interactive e-learning platform for theoretical components

In-person practical training at our clinical classroom and laboratory

Externship/clinical rotation at partnering hospitals and health institutions nationwide

This approach ensures flexibility, hands-on competence, and real-world experience essential for success in today's healthcare environment.
